      "span_text": "In the first experiment, 50 Romney sheep (G1; 19 male and 31 female) and 50 Suffolk sheep (G2; 37 male and 13 female), (G2) of the ARQ/ARQ PRNP genotype (A, alanine, R, arginine and Q, glutamine at codons 136, 154 and 171 of PrP, respectively) were orally dosed at three and six months of age, respectively, with the same cattle-derived BSE inoculum (brain pool from clinically affected, BSE-confirmed cattle), as used in a previously described experiment [CITATION_1] .",
